  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "The Founding Omnibus collects the first three Gaunt's Ghosts novels — First and Only, Ghostmaker and Necropolis — and tells the story of how Colonel-Commissar Ibram Gaunt and the Tanith First-and-Only become the unit that will carry the Sabbat Worlds Crusade. Book one (First and Only) follows the early Crusade-era campaigns from Voltemand through Pyrites and Fortis Binary to the Menazoid Epsilon stalemate, establishing the regiment's cast and the internal-Imperium conspiracy run by Lord General Dravere and the Jantine Patricians. Book two (Ghostmaker), structured as a fix-up of linked Inferno!-magazine flashbacks framed by a present-tense Monthax campaign, gives each principal Ghost — Corbec, Rawne, Larkin, Bragg, Caffran, Mkoll, Milo, Dorden — a single-protagonist spotlight chapter, peeling the regiment's mythology open one trooper at a time and closing on a brief tactical truce with an Eldar warhost. Book three (Necropolis) is the Vervunhive siege on Verghast: the Zoican Host under Heritor Asphodel besieges Vervunhive, multiple Imperial regiments arrive piecemeal under squabbling generals, Gaunt is forced to take command of the relief, and the regiment's second intake — the Verghastite Ghosts, founded inside a burning city — permanently changes the unit's character.",
